{{For|other uses of Jalal Khan|Jalal Khan (disambiguation)}}
'''Jalal Khan''' ({{lang-ur|'''جلال خان'''}}) is a legendary figure in the history of the [[Baloch people]] who led the Baloch from [[Persia]] to [[Makran]].<ref>Sabir Badal Khan, ''Two Essays on Baloch History and Folklore'', (Università di Napoli, "l'Orientale", 2013), 49-50. </ref>

Khan had four sons, Rind, Hot, Lashari, and Korai, and a daughter, Jato.<ref>Sabir Badal Khan, ''Two Essays on Baloch History and Folklore'', 20.</ref> [[Baloch tribes]] derive their eponymous names from Khan's children.

